messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I have a... Okay. I'm at Wildcat Haven. We've had one of our keepers get attacked. I need an ambulance.
Okay. I'm going to get you over to the correct fire dispatch. Just one moment for me, okay?
I understand, sir.
I don't dispatch medical for that area. I'm transferring you. Stay on the line, okay?
Please hurry.
We are hurrying.
I'm with medical transfer, 31369 Southwest Heater Road at Wildcat Haven. I'm going to stay on the line and monitor in case any police need information. Go ahead, sir.
Hello? I'm going on. I have a keeper at Wildcat Haven who was attacked, I guess. I just got home here, and I think she's dead, but please hurry.
How was she attacked?
We have cougars. We rescue them.
By a cougar, I believe?
Yes. I'm going back down. I need you guys here. I've got to go back down to her.
She's down in the enclosure?
Yes. I'm going down to get her.
Can you hear me?
Yeah, I can hear you. I'm on a cordless phone. It's going to run out in a minute here.
Okay, she's in the cat enclosure?
She's in the cat enclosure. I'm going to get her out if I can. I'm going to lose you here.
I can hear you, yes. We're on our way. How do we get in the gate?
I can't see. I'm going back down. It's dark.
Are you in a safe position to be able to go in by yourself?
No, I'm here.
Okay, we don't want you to get hurt.
I hear what you're saying. Get out of here! Oh my God! Oh my God, oh my God, oh my God!
We have help on the way over there to you. Are you in the enclosure right now?
I'm back out.
Is your friend still in the enclosure?
I got her out.
Can we try CPR or is she beyond help?
No, she's gone.
What's your name, sir?
Mark Powell.
Is anyone else in danger at this point?
Nobody's in danger.
So you think that she is beyond help?
Yes, I do.
I'm sorry. Can I start getting support over for you to talk to, like a chaplain or something? Can I call somebody for you?
I don't know.
Hello?
